snippet.textDisplay: hey Nile love your video. Quick tip I should tell you about how to carbonate water with dry ice easily. When I was younger and had some dry ice i put it in a cup of water and walked around joking I was drinking it. Then I remembered I accidentally left another cup with dry ice and water downstairs in the garage. When I looked, the water was bubbling and I wafted and smell carbonated water. I used this method to make some bubbly water every time I got dry ice. But if i was you and tried this maybe put a cover over the lid of the cup and monitor it to make sure it doesn't build up to much so you don't loose diamonds and this comment is way longer than I wanted it to be reply yeet yes if you read this whole thing.

I dont know what you paid for it obviously but im guessing it was probably the actual price of it, that stuffs not cheap depending on what spec it is. Any stainless pressure setup is going to get expensive very quickly. Not meaning to be a keyboard warrior or anything im just offering a little info so maybe your wallet can relax a little. I absolutely love your channel man you have some of the best content on here!
P.S. i appreciate that your not afraid of the unkown. To my eyes there were one or two things that i would have done differently with the CO2 rig but thats just me being technical, other than that you did a fantastic job with it especially with this being your first(?) apparatus!
